The paper proposes a novel multi-task learning framework that prioritizes tasks and instances based on their complexities, which is a common problem in machine learning. This suggests that the paper could belong to several sub-categories, including cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.CV (Computer Vision), cs.CL (Computation and Language), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). However, given that the proposed framework is primarily focused on learning from multiple tasks, cs.LG is the most likely sub-category. The other sub-categories are also relevant because the proposed framework can be applied to various tasks, including computer vision, natural language processing, and neural networks.
